{"type":"message","id":"5022bb55","parentId":"6972ae0c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:52:40.879Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_obzpqwd8p3b8_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[32;1mName                      [0m[32;1m LastWriteTime[0m\r\n[32;1m----                      [0m [32;1m-------------[0m\r\npulse_2026-03-24 005115.md 3/24/2026 12:51:46 AM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 004916.md 3/24/2026 12:49:38 AM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 004715.md 3/24/2026 12:47:40 AM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 004513.md 3/24/2026 12:46:14 AM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 004214.md 3/24/2026 12:42:43 AM"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":579,"aggregated":"[32;1mName                      [0m[32;1m LastWriteTime[0m\r\n[32;1m----                      [0m [32;1m-------------[0m\r\npulse_2026-03-24 005115.md 3/24/2026 12:51:46 AM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 004916.md 3/24/2026 12:49:38 AM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 004715.md 3/24/2026 12:47:40 AM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 004513.md 3/24/2026 12:46:14 AM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 004214.md 3/24/2026 12:42:43 AM","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774327960877}}
{"type":"message","id":"8cca8f1a","parentId":"5022bb55","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:52:43.468Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"A new pulse log was created at 005115 - let me read that one.","thinkingSignature":"f917dd3bb9672edda36944e5a1b13259944e000fc0ea3b26eca1f595b31d2d2a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p0ymkctfwghc_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 005115.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3969,"output":71,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15994,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774327960880}}
{"type":"message","id":"d010aeeb","parentId":"8cca8f1a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:52:43.475Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_p0ymkctfwghc_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 005115\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. Key insight: Compression-Causal Duality has been identified\r\n3. Next action: TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n4. Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe pending action is clear: Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\nI should create a script or module that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs (last 20)\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant or variant\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Measures accuracy against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction)\r\n\r\nLet me check what's in the logs directory to understand the structure of pulse logs.\r\n\r\nSince this is a stateless discontinuous agent, I need to be specific about a concrete action. The most immediate next step for the TIC experiment would be to create the TIC classifier implementation.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that will:\r\n1. Load recent pulse logs\r\n2. Implement the invariant/variant classification\r\n3. Run the experiment\r\n4. Output results\r\n\r\nI'll write a `tic_experiment.py` script.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the immediate next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can distinguish invariant (causal) vs variant content across pulse logs, then measure prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment script that loads pulse logs, classifies invariant vs variant content, measures classification accuracy, and attempts next-pulse prediction. This directly addresses the pending \"Implement TIC classifier\" task.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs(n=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Load last n pulse logs sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = []\r\n    for f in sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), reverse=True)[:n]:\r\n        logs.append(f.read_text())\r\n    return list(reversed(logs))  # Chronological order\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_blocks(log_text):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract major content blocks from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    blocks = []\r\n    # Extract sections: OBSERVATION, ACTION, MUTATION, thinking\r\n    sections = re.split(r\"\\n(?=### )\", log_text)\r\n    for s in sections:\r\n        s = s.strip()\r\n        if s and len(s) > 20:\r\n            blocks.append(s)\r\n    return blocks\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariant_score(block, all_blocks):\r\n    \"\"\"Score how 'invariant' a block is across all pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    # Invariant = appears repeatedly with similar structure\r\n    # Variant = unique or rapidly changing\r\n    \r\n    # Simple heuristic: word overlap with other blocks\r\n    words = set(re.findall(r'\\b\\w{4,}\\b', block.lower()))\r\n    if not words:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    \r\n    overlaps = []\r\n    for other in all_blocks:\r\n        if other == block:\r\n            continue\r\n        other_words = set(re.findall(r'\\b\\w{4,}\\b', other.lower()))\r\n        if other_words:\r\n            overlap = len(words & other_words) / len(words)\r\n            overlaps.append(overlap)\r\n    \r\n    if overlaps:\r\n        return sum(overlaps) / len(overlaps)\r\n    return 0.0\r\n\r\ndef classify_blocks(logs):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify blocks as invariant (>0.4 score) or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    all_blocks = []\r\n    for log in logs:\r\n        all_blocks.extend(extract_content_blocks(log))\r\n    \r\n    # Deduplicate\r\n    all_blocks = list(dict.fromkeys(all_blocks))\r\n    \r\n    results = []\r\n    for block in all_blocks:\r\n        score = compute_invariant_score(block, all_blocks)\r\n        classification = \"INVARIANT\" if score > 0.4 else \"VARIANT\"\r\n        results.append((block[:100], score, classification))\r\n    \r\n    return results, all_blocks\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariant_blocks, target_log):\r\n    \"\"\"Attempt to predict content of target pulse from invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    target_blocks = extract_content_blocks(target_log)\r\n    predicted = []\r\n    \r\n    for inv_block in invariant_blocks:\r\n        # Check if invariant patterns appear in target\r\n        inv_words = set(re.findall(r'\\b\\w{4,}\\b', inv_block.lower()))\r\n        for t_block in target_blocks:\r\n            t_words = set(re.findall(r'\\b\\w{4,}\\b', t_block.lower()))\r\n            if inv_words and t_words:\r\n                overlap = len(inv_words & t_words) / len(inv_words)\r\n                if overlap > 0.3:\r\n                    predicted.append(inv_block[:50])\r\n                    break\r\n    \r\n    return predicted\r\n\r\ndef run_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Execute TIC experiment and report results.\"\"\"\r\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\r\n    print(\"TIC EXPERIMENT - Temporal Invariance Compression\")\r\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\r\n    \r\n    logs = load_pulse_logs(20)\r\n    print(f\"\\nLoaded {len(logs)} pulse logs\")\r\n    \r\n    if len(logs) < 5:\r\n        print(\"ERROR: Need at least 5 logs for meaningful experiment\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    #\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:51:46\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774327963473}}
{"type":"message","id":"bd63541b","parentId":"d010aeeb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:53:00.821Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have both pulse logs. Let me summarize what happened in this pulse cycle:\n\n1. **pulse_2026-03-24 004916.md** (12:49:38 AM):\n   - Observed that TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step\n   - Created a mutation to implement a TIC classifier script (Python)\n   - Exit code 1 - the mutation was malformed/partial\n\n2. **pulse_2026-03-24 005115.md** (12:51:46 AM):\n   - Attempted to create the Python script for TIC experiment\n   - The mutation was still incomplete/malformed\n   - Exit code 1 - also didn't complete successfully\n\nThe pattern here seems to be that the sandbox is trying to create the TIC experiment script, but the Python mutation keeps getting truncated or malformed. The `old_text: (new file)` and `new_text: the` indicates the Python parser failed to properly extract the file content from the LLM output.\n\nThe sandbox is running but having issues creating new files - the mutations are being truncated. This is a recurring issue where the file creation content is too long and gets cut off.","thinkingSignature":"462c6f976c76d4aeb1844c9411e35b94f392fec90af309c23369939913b01e1d"},{"type":"text","text":"## Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 00:51 UTC\n\n**Pulse #005115** (12:51:46 AM ET) — ⚠️ **Exit code 1 (malformed mutation)**\n\n### What Happened\n\nThe sandbox ran two consecutive pulses targeting the **TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment**:\n\n1. **Pulse 004916 (12:49 AM)** — Attempted to create a PowerShell TIC classifier script. The mutation was **truncated mid-write**: the Python parser extracted `old_text: (new file)` but `new_text` came out as just `\"the\"` — the full file content was cut off. Exit code 1.\n\n2. **Pulse 005115 (12:51 AM)** — Tried again with a Python implementation (`tic_experiment.py`). Same pattern: the file content got **malformed at the Python extraction step**. The `old_text` and `new_text` fields were incomplete, causing the mutation to fail. Exit code 1 again.\n\n### Root Issue\n\nThe **mutation parser** is choking on long file content — when the LLM outputs a new file with substantial body text, the `old_text=(new file)` / `new_text=<content>` parsing fails to capture the full content, truncating to just a fragment (`\"the\"`).\n\n### Observed State\n\nThe sandbox is still in **Phase 1** — actively trying to implement the TIC experiment but hitting a file-creation bottleneck. The compression-causal duality insight (`causal structure = invariant structure`) has been identified but not yet validated experimentally.\n\n### For Next Instantiation\n\n- **Proposed mutations waiting:** 1 (the TIC Python script)\n- **Fix needed:** The mutation parser needs a different approach for creating new files — either chunk the content or use a different file creation mechanism that doesn't rely on old/new text extraction"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5350,"output":631,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17935,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774327963476}}
